The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 April is 41,715 (4,828.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 April, there were 127 new confirmed cases (14.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 April, there were 134 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 5% (7 fewer cases).
